examples.en: The road rises steeply from the village.
The path began to climb steeply upwards.
The street rose steeply up to the castle.
After climbing steeply, the path levelled off.
The Australian dollar isnt likely to fall steeply.
Few analysts foresaw that oil prices would rise so steeply.
At this point the road upturns steeply, the trees become scarcer, and the valley unfolds before you.
They sloped our new driveway too steeply and now my car scrapes bottom whenever I back out onto the street.
